{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1782a02a-fac9-4806-a3e2-9a50a71eb9fc","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`)\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you assert on the exception's properties (message, param name, inner exception)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0c014a3d-0033-484c-9e43-590b0ba1e033","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":247,"requestId":"1BDC:220345:6C4864A:74ED5B0:6A03D5FA"},"id":"5b0c1aca-637d-4ba7-8f55-cfefed1e060d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:38:10.067Z","parentId":"36e6e2d5-b6bc-48af-8816-0b68bd481a8e"}
